name: BMO US Aggregate Bond Index ETF
longDescription: The ETF has been designed to replicate, to the extent possible, the performance of the Bloomberg US Aggregate Bond Index, net of expenses. The fund invests in a variety of debt securities with at least one year remaining to maturity. Securities held in the index are a broad measure of the U.S. fixed income market.
